Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks were held at the head office of the Czech Newspaper Dialog and in Byalystok City of Poland on Mar.
17 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun and the 12th anniversary of the election of leader Kim Jong Il as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and the 73rd founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army. 
 Zdenek Novotny, consultant chief editor of Dialog, said President  Kim Il Sung was a great revolutionary who hewed the path of the Korean revolution and led the Korean people to victory and a great leader of the world revolution who made a distinguished contribution to the cause of socialism and independence in the world and set a brilliant example in the anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jiri Jarka, chairman of the Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association, noted that Kim Jong Il put forward the unique Songun political mode, reliably defending socialism and the sovereignty of the country with the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Slaboy January Guzowski, representative of the Central Committee of the Poland-Korea Association, said that if one analyzes the current international situation one can realize that the justice and vitality of the Juche idea fathered by Kim Il Sung and the Songun politics pursuing by  Kim Jong Il have been proved. The Korean people are happy to hold the two great leaders in high esteem, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the round-table talks praised the Songun politics of the DPRK as the most just political mode which should be applied without fail to defend and strengthen socialism. The DPRK's access to nuclear weapons is an entirely just self-defensive measure to cope with the U.S. escalating moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK, they noted.

Photo Exhibitions Held in Democratic Congo and Peru 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Photo exhibitions were held in various countries on March 22 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun and the 12th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the National Defence Commission of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Displayed at a photo exhibition in Democratic Congo were photographs showing immortal leadership exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, advantages of the socialist system in the DPRK and achievements made by it in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers there referred to the immortal exploits, the preeminent strategy and tactics and wise leadership of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, adding that they are saviors of the Korean people. 
 The Internet homepage of the Peru Group for the Study of Kimilsungism inaugurated the first photo exhibition "Socialism of Juche" and "The Great Prosperous Powerful Socialist Nation of Juche." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The photo exhibition will be arranged on important holidays and occasions of the DPRK till the end of December.

Many Inventors Produced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang IT College has produced more than 120 inventors and at least 220 persons of ingenuity at a time.
 They are teachers, researchers and students of the college. They have advanced lots of valuable invention and innovation proposals conducive to the technological updating of the national economy and the modernization of educational and experimental equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are a digital control system at a spark-erosion metal working machine, Gregorian escalating digital alternating current voltage regulator, an analyzer of 16 channels logic time chart and state and support system for teaching how to set a homepage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These draw attention of officials and technicians of the relevant field for their unique idea, feasibility to put them into practice and economic profitability.

Educational HQ, of S. Prep.Com. for Joint Functions Inaugurated in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Educational Headquarters of the South Preparatory Committee for Joint Functions of Koreans in the South and the North and Overseas to implement the June 15 joint declaration was reportedly held in Seoul on March 25.
 Present at the ceremony were members of the south Korean Teachers Union (Jongyojo) and the south Korean General Association of Teachers Organizations (Kyochong) and personages of other circles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Chairman of Jongyojo Ri Su Il and Chairman of Kyochong Yun Jong Gon were elected co-representatives of the educational headquarters and Chairwoman of the Unification Committee of Jongyojo Pak Mi Ja and Chairman of the South-North Educational Exchange Committee of Kyochong Han Yong Man executive co-chairpersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony speeches were made and an inaugural declaration was read out.

Preparatory Com. for Eliminating Leftover of Japan's Rule Formed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- A preparatory committee was reportedly inaugurated at Seoul National University on March 23 to eliminate the leftover of the Japanese imperialists' rule.
 A press conference on its inauguration was held at the Students' Hall of the university on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers there said that the truth has been refuted as the issue of pro-Japanese acts has been justified at the university. They resolved to conduct a full-scale movement to liquidate pro-Japanese elements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An action program of the organization was made public there.

Japanese Right-wing Forces Urged to Halt Their Moves to Grab Tok Islet
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary strongly denounces the dangerous moves of the Japanese ultra-right conservative forces to grab Tok Islet.
 The commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These days the Japanese ultra-right conservative forces are insisting that Tok Islet "belongs to the territory" of Japan. This once again proves that they are greedy robbers who stoop to any infamy to realize their territorial expansion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This move assumes graver nature as it is stepped up, timed to coincide with their distortion of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 History will never change and disappear no matter how hard they work to tamper with and cover up it. History remains as it is despite the change of the era and the flow of the time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese ultra-right conservative forces' moves to seize Tok Islet and distort history are hardening the resolution and will of the army and people of the DPRK to settle accounts with Japan to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people reserve the legitimate right to get an apology and compensation from Japan for its forcible drafting of Koreans, massacre of them, the sexual slavery for the imperial Japanese army, the policy of forcing Koreans to change their names to Japanese and other crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foolish of the ultra-right conservative forces of Japan to go wild to distort history and grab Tok Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They had better stop behaving so.

Japan Hit for Obliterating Korean Language
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday carries a signed article disclosing that the policy of obliterating the Korean language enforced by the Japanese imperialists during their 40-odd-year-long colonial rule over Korea was a grave state-sponsored crime committed by Japan's state ruling machinery on the strength of ordinances.
 The Japanese imperialists persistently talked about "the Korean and Japanese nations forming a harmonious whole," chanting the slogans for the "conversion of Koreans into imperial subjects" and "Japanization of Koreans" with a view to reducing Koreans to their slaves, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During their occupation of Korea they formed a strong state ruling system to obliterate the Korean language. To this end, they set in motion even gendarmes, to say nothing of the administrative and police organs including the "Korean Government-General", provincial, county and sub-county offices, police stations, sub-stations and police boxes. They officially declared that Japanese would be used as an official language at all government and public offices, courts and others. They unhesitatingly proclaimed that
Japanese was the "mother tongue" to be compulsorily used by Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They promulgated the "law on editing newspapers" in 1907, the "press law" in 1909 and the "press regulations" in 1910, thus tightening the measures to obliterate the national identity of the Korean people and the Korean language. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They fabricated the "ordinance on Korean education" and retrogressively revised it four times in a bid to step up their policy of obliterating the Korean language. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This policy was harshly pursued in all fabrics of social life including family life, not to speak of education, press, radio broadcasting, drama, film, music, linguistics and other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They forced the "Korean Association of Literary Men" to rename it the "Korean Society of Literary Men for Protecting the Country" in 1942, pressurized Korean men of literature to join it and write every work in the "mother tongue." They made sure that its organ Kukmin Munhak, too, was published in Japanese. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They promulgated the "ordinance" related to "the change of Korean names into Japanese" in 1939 before intensifying their suppression of Koreans. All the ruling machines from the "Korean Government-General" to provincial, county and sub-county offices and police stations and sub-stations and pro-Japanese organizations did their utmost to thoroughly execute the ordinance in those days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such acts perpetrated by the Japanese imperialists to obliterate the Korean language and national identity during their unheard-of colonial fascist rule were the most brutal and horrible mental tortures and hideous crimes committed against the Korean people.

U.S. Plan Falcon Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Some days ago the commander of the Space Command of the U.S. Air Force, addressing the Armed Services Committee of
the U.S. House of Representatives, opened to the public the U.S. plan codenamed Falcon to have the capacity to strike any part of the world.
 The plan Falcon is part of the U.S. adventurous moves to establish the sphere of its military domination over the whole world and this is very dangerous as it will spark a new arms race and Cold War, says Minju Joson Tuesday in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration is now busy developing nukes and modernizing them and establishing the missile defense system despite the opposition and rebuff of the broad international community. Not content with this, it is contemplating developing means to strike any part of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. unilateral, high-handed and arbitrary military actions in the international arena are heightening the vigilance of many countries. It is, therefore, as clear as noonday that the U.S. moves for military supremacy would spark a new arms race worldwide and foster confrontation due to military conflicts and frictions and this would lead to a new Cold War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. reckless moves for military supremacy are seriously upsetting military balance, disturbing stability and aggravating the military confrontation in various countries and regions of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 World public is unanimous in observing that the U.S. policy for military supremacy over the whole world is an anachronistic dream based on its outdated way of thinking. The U.S. would be well advised to face up to the reality and drop at once its foolish dream to dominate the world by force.

Bumper Kelp Crop in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 29 (KCNA) -- Kelp harvest is in full swing on the offshore farms on the west coast of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 As of the end of March the farms under the Fishery Complex of South Hwanghae Province have reaped kelp 3.7 times that in the corresponding period of last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pupho Offshore Farm has overfulfilled its kelp production plan for March by properly thinning out kelp and increasing output per kelp-growing rope. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Phyonghwa Offshore Farm is carrying out the daily kelp production quota at 104 percent by raising the operation rate of boats to suit the sea weather conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar achievements have also been made by the Ongjin and Kumipho Offshore Farms and Monggumpho Fishery Station.
